        "comment": "The avalanche prone locations are to be found adjacent to ridgelines and in gullies and bowls and at transitions from a shallow to a deep snowpack. Avalanches can penetrate down to the ground. They can in many places be released, even by a single winter sport participant.  Wooded areas could also be affected by avalanches and present situations of instability. Moist avalanches are possible as a consequence of warming.",
